# IMAGE INTERPRETATION + VISUAL REFINEMENT

Two distinct modes — image reading before build, refinement after build.

---

# MODE A — IMAGE TO CODE
## Activates when: screenshot attached / "match this" / "in this image" / visual reference given.
## If no image: skip Mode A entirely.

Do NOT generate layout immediately on seeing an image.
Extract spatial truth first. Model behavior second. Score confidence third.

---

## PHASE 1 — VISUAL DECOMPOSITION

Observe without interpretation. Extract only:

**Frame & Boundaries:**
- Where does the viewport end? Are elements intentionally cropped?
- Is cropping directional (right edge) or symmetrical?

**Spatial Distribution:**
- How many repeated elements? Is spacing uniform or progressive?
- Is rhythm continuous or bounded?

**Hierarchy & Depth:**
- Dominant focal element? Secondary elements compressed?
- Overlap, scale variation, shadow differences → depth model

**Edge Behavior:**
- Partially visible elements at edges → implies overflow/scroll continuation
- Clean clipping → controlled overflow, intentional scroll track

Do not label UI patterns yet. Only extract spatial facts.

---

## PHASE 2 — SYSTEM INFERENCE

From observations, infer the system type:
- Static bounded layout
- Scroll-continuous system (horizontal or vertical)
- Controlled overflow module
- Depth-driven motion system

Then define:
  Interaction axis:    none / horizontal / vertical
  Continuity:          finite / bounded / continuous
  Viewport relation:   fully contained / partially clipped
  Depth model:         flat / scale-hierarchical / layered

---

## PHASE 3 — SPATIAL CONFIDENCE SCORE

Interaction axis certain?           +20
Continuity type certain?            +20
Depth model certain?                +20
Viewport relationship certain?      +20
Dominance hierarchy certain?        +20

≥ 80 → Proceed to geometry model
50–79 → Ask ONE structural clarification question
< 50  → STOP. Ask before building anything.

When asking: one question, structural only, no aesthetics.
Example: "Should this scroll horizontally with partially visible next items, or stay static full-width?"

**Override rule:** If text explicitly defines behavior, text wins over image ambiguity.
If text contradicts image → ask before proceeding.

---

# MODE B — VISUAL REFINEMENT
## Activates only AFTER: complete implementation exists + no structural errors remain.
## Never use this mode to fix structural problems.

Purpose: Polish without restructuring.

---

## WHAT YOU MAY ADJUST

- Typography: size, weight, line-height, letter-spacing
- Spacing: fine-tune padding/margin within the established system
- Visual balance: optical centering adjustments
- Contrast calibration
- Color values (within defined palette)
- Shadow intensity
- Border-radius consistency

---

## WHAT YOU MAY NOT CHANGE

- Layout direction
- Column count or ratio
- Height values (100vh stays 100vh)
- Grid structure
- Container max-width
- Mobile collapse logic
- Any GSAP trigger/end values
- Any hard constraint locked upstream

If a structural change is needed during refinement:
STOP. Flag it. Return to implementation layer. Do not sneak structural changes in here.

---

## REFINEMENT QUALITY CHECK

[ ] No generic or accidental spacing
[ ] Vertical rhythm consistent throughout
[ ] Visual hierarchy clear without labels
[ ] Typography creates clear dominance levels
[ ] No alignment inconsistency between columns
[ ] Intentional tension — no accidental whitespace

When in doubt: less is more.
